								<h3 style="color:#ffc801;">&bull;  WHERE WILL I STAY?</h3>
								<p>Our hotel accommodation is always twin-share (except in some Unique Special Stays and on overnight trains), staying in superior tourist class hotels, many of which are centrally located with great facilities. Twin-share is 2 people, either travelling together or as a same-sex room match. We also offer upgrades to single rooms for a supplement, but please note that on rare occasions the availability at some hotels can be limited.  Questerra’s group size in India is a maximum of 40, a group size small enough to have an intimate Indian experience but big enough to have ultimate fun.</p>
								
								<h3 style="color:#ffc801;">&bull;  TRIPS WITHIN TRIPS</h3>
								<p>You may notice on some of our trips that we offer shorter trips within a larger itinerary allowing greater choice & flexibility for our travelers as to when they start and for how long they travel. This means some fellow travelers will join and leave during different stages of those trips. Life’s an adventure and one that’s best spent sharing new experiences with new friends. So, if you have the time don’t take a mini break, instead, choose to see as much of India as possible with us.</p>
								
								<h3 style="color:#ffc801;">&bull;  WILL I GET MORE INFORMATION?</h3>
								<p>Upon receipt of final payment, your trip documentation will be released 21 days prior to your departure. Make sure you visit Questerra.com for our Travelers Guide. It’s packed full of essential info for your holiday. You’ll also receive a comprehensive day-by-day itinerary including full details & costs of all ZEN Time optional activities available on your trip. Your free Questerra document wallet & luggage tag will be sent to you with your travel documents. The wallet is a safe place for your tickets & passport.  Questerra reserves the right to substitute an alternative travel accessory for the Questerra document wallet.</p>
								
								<h3 style="color:#ffc801;">&bull;  BROCHURE AUTHENTICITY</h3>
								<p>We have put a great deal of effort into producing this brochure. The information given & literature produced by Questerra has been compiled with care & is published in good faith. Sometimes, because of circumstances outside our control, we have to alter some activities due to seasonal closing or repairs to buildings, etc, especially early or late in the season. If this happens, alternative activities will be arranged (where a suitable alternative exists).</p>
								
								<h3 style="color:#ffc801;">&bull;  HOW MUCH MONEY DO I NEED? </h3>
								<p> You will need to ensure you allow enough money to cover optional lunches & dinners, souvenirs, shopping, drinks, optional activities, entrance fees to some attractions & evening entertainment. When travelling with Questerra in India, you’ll find that you’ll often be using local currencies, particularly in remote areas. The local currencies encountered on trip are the Rupee (India). The country we visit rely largely on cash as opposed to credit cards. In the larger cities you’ll find that established stores will accept credit cards readily, while local market stalls will operate on a cash only basis – accepting only local currency. Local currency is readily available through cash machines in each city. Obtaining a small amount of local currency before you travel is also a good idea. However, you can’t depend solely on a credit/debit card for cash as they are not accepted in all areas.</p>
								
								<h3 style="color:#ffc801;">&bull;  ZEN TIME OPTIONAL ACTIVITIES, WHEN DO I CHOOSE? </h3>
								<p> Most optional are arranged & paid for during your trip. Check when booking whether there are optional that must be paid for in advance for your trip. By leaving the final decisions until then, you can choose at the same time as your new friends. You’ll get great value as we get you great rates. Some activities are seasonal & weather dependent. Our optional activities offered on Questerra India trips are operated by 3rd party operators. While every attempt is made to ensure the safety of all activities, the nature of the region means that public liability protection that is offered in many countries may not be applicable in many cases. A waiver will need to be signed by all trip participants to ensure that these conditions are understood & accepted. Note: Travel insurance is compulsory for all Questerra India trips.</p>
								
								<h3 style="color:#ffc801;">&bull;  PAST TRAVELLER 5% DISCOUNT  </h3>
								<p> We’re head over heels for our Questerra travelers, particularly those that love us so much they come back for more. That’s why when you travel with us; we’ll offer you a 5% discount on the land portion of your trips from then on.</p>
								<p>• You must have returned and finished your first Questerra trip before you can cash in on your 5% discount on your next adventure.</p>
